                     <origDate notBefore="1850" notAfter="1900" instant="false">The colophon indicates that the Ms. was completed on the 14th year after the coronation of King Bäkaffa, but he ruled only 9 years (1721-30); it contains also two other dates which appear to be incorrect. Despite the information in the colophon, the script does not look so old palaeographically. The Ms. may date into a later period, second half of the 19th cent. The binding (boards covered with tooled leather) appears to be older than the text block. The Ms. (and the colophon) may be a copy of another 18th-cent. Ms. of Haymanot ʾabäw.</origDate>
